crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a downloader/dropper. It establishes persistence by copying itself to a special folder as 'AcroRd32Info.exe' and ensures a single instance by creating a mutex ('5ed7f8a9-ba28-4b41-89ac-702e5fa5ab24'). It then deobfuscates a C2 domain ('www.kbsitjc.com') and URI ('/syouisyu/image/s/php') using a simple substitution cipher. It communicates with the C2 to download an additional payload, which is encoded with a custom Base64 alphabet. The malware decodes this payload, saves it to a new executable in the Temp directory (e.g., 'igfxHK<random>.exe'), and executes it.
